dc_title_s: West Indies, Hispaniola--south coast, Dominican Republic, Isla Beata to Isla Saona (Raster Image)
dc_description_s: Prepared and published by the Defense Mapping Agency Hydrographic/Topographic Center. Depths shown by isolines and soundings. Relief shown by contours and spot heights. "From surveys by the USNS Harkness in 1975 and 1976, with additions from other sources to 1969; shoreline and topography from other sources to 1970." "Copyright 1995 by the United States government. No copyright claimed under title 17 U.S.C." "Soundings in meters." Inset: Approaches to Santo Domingo. Scale 1:100,000. Includes compilation diagram. Map no.25800 This map is part of a collection of scanned and georeferenced nautical charts produced by the National Geospatial-Intelligence Agency (NGA).
